                        <interp inst="t18470614-name-1095" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN GRIFFIN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 229.) I apprehended the prisoner on the 3rd of June—I told him he was charged with stealing a watch from the prosecutor—he replied that he had settled matters with the prosecutor—I said I should take him to the station, and I asked what he had done with the watch—he said he had pawned it at Greenwich, and had lost the duplicate—he did not tell me at what shop he pawned it.</p>
